Evaluation Test 1- Weather Info & Forecast Bot using Google
Dialogflow ES

Use Case
You are required to build a chatbot using Google Dialogflow ES that can provide current and
forecasted global weather information to its users.
● Thebotwill be able to provide current weather information for a specific city.
● Thebotwill be able to provide forecasted weather information for up to the next 8 days
from the current date for a specific city

Objectives
1. Setup and configure Dialogflow ES:
a. Build the conversational flow as shown in the sequence diagram provided
below.
b. Configure fulfillment webhook. (URL of your hosted code on any hosting service
i.e ngrok)

2. Build a REST API that can receive a webhook request from the Weather bot that you’ve
built in Step 1. (Use backend language/framework of your choice)
a. Receive the WebhookRequest from the bot and fetch the location (city) and
date that the user has provided.
i. Time should be fetched automatically from chat session details.
ii. If no date is provided, current weather information will be relevant based
on the chat session date.
iii. From the start date calculate 8 days ahead to provide the forecasted
weather

b. Use this resource and its APIs to fetch the data.
c. Return the response back to the bot and show it in the Dialogflow Chat interface.

